FBIS4-41811 "drsov124_f_94019" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 National Affairs Special-Purpose Battalion Said Undernourished, Underpaid Special-Purpose Battalion Said Undernourished, Underpaid AU2706131294 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 24 Jun 94 p 1 AU2706131294 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY Ukrainian BFN [Unattributed report published under the rubric "Fact"] [Text] Foreign specialists, who visited the "White Panther" [Bila Pantera] special-purpose battalion within the Kiev regiment of Ukraine's National Guard, were highly impressed by the level of training of the guards. One can imagine how surprised they might be if they had learned that the special-purpose guards' nourishment is worse than that of regular servicemen and that the average pay received by the commander of the battalion constitutes 400,000 coupons a month.
